        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39008",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Your example give an exception:\r\n\r\n\"Fatal error: Uncaught exception 'Zend_Date_Exception' with message 'Unable to parse date '31 Dec 2036' using 'dd.MM.yyyy HH:mm:ss' \"\r\n\r\nThis is no problem of Zend_Date as you define to use dd.MM.yyyy HH:mm:ss bus you give dd MMM yyyy.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-05T14:48:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-05T14:48:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39009",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Reducing from Critical to Minor...\r\nExample failes by design.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-05T14:50:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-05T14:50:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39012",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=k2s",
                        "name": "k2s",
                        "displayName": "Martin Minka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thomas,\r\nhave you visited my working example at http:\/\/www.k2s.sk\/grid\/date.php ?\r\n\r\nThe code should work for you if you change:\r\n{code}\r\n$date = new Zend_Date($str);\r\n{code}\r\nto\r\n{code}\r\n$date = new Zend_Date($str, \"dd MMM yy\"); \r\n{code}\r\n\r\n*Zend_Date is not reliable on future dates and that is in my opinion critical bug.*\r\n\r\nThe error you are getting is not relevant to the problem I am describing and which is easily to see at http:\/\/www.k2s.sk\/grid\/date.php. I think it is caused by some locale configuration differences.\r\n\r\nI found the problem, I am trying to show here, on many forums, but without solutions. The time is shifted in Europa\/London timezone in very strange way on some dates.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=k2s",
                        "name": "k2s",
                        "displayName": "Martin Minka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-05T16:15:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-05T16:15:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39013",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=k2s",
                        "name": "k2s",
                        "displayName": "Martin Minka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "_I think it is caused by some locale configuration differences._ - is related to the error you are getting with my code, I don't know why Zend_Date has problems with some dates in some timezones.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=k2s",
                        "name": "k2s",
                        "displayName": "Martin Minka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-05T16:18:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-05T16:18:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39203",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Also the online example fails by design.\r\nIt returns the same exception as when running it locally.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-13T02:43:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-13T02:43:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39222",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=k2s",
                        "name": "k2s",
                        "displayName": "Martin Minka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "ok, I tested the example with IE set to use Language germany and you are right it fails, because of the Month name parsin.\r\n\r\nI added following code to force Zend_Date to use english to parse the month names:\r\n{code}\r\n\/\/ don't use locale detected from browser to understand month names\r\nrequire \"Zend\/Registry.php\";\r\n$locale = new Zend_Locale(\"en_GB\");\r\nZend_Registry::set(\"Zend_Locale\", $locale);\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nIt should work now for you now here: http:\/\/www.k2s.sk\/grid\/date.php\r\n\r\nIf for any other reason it will not work, pls. download the output here: http:\/\/www.k2s.sk\/grid\/dateproblem.pdf",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=k2s",
                        "name": "k2s",
                        "displayName": "Martin Minka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-14T08:06:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-14T08:06:37.000+0000"
                }
            ]
